## Getting Started
@@ -32,9 +32,15 @@ _Below is an example of how to install the tool in your

1. Clone the repo
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/niveussolutions/Swagger-tool.git
   ```

2. Open the terminal inside downloaded Swagger-tool project file
   And install the packages with NPM
   ```sh
npm install
   ```
   Or
   ```sh
npm i
   ```
3. Open the terminal inside downloaded Swagger-tool project file
   Run the project
   ```sh
   ts-node-esm run.ts "home/download/your_postman_collection.json"
   ```
4. If your collection/Collection path is correct it will generate the swagger doc structure inside the output/output.yaml file 
**_NOTE:_**  output.yaml file is inside your project folder and confirm the structure using swagger once 

